12/12/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis said Friday (10 December) the government is resolute in fighting corruption and eliminating all windows of opportunity for corrupt practices and officials. 
Within days, the government plans to submit a bill to parliament restricting the access of companies to public contracts. 
The bill also stipulates that all media companies must register their shareholders. 
Karamanlis pledged the new administration would not bow to outside pressure in its fight against corruption. 
(Kathimerini - 11/12/04)
